<!-- Section 1 -->
<section class="section">
    <div class="container">
        <h2 class="text-center mb-4">Overview of Cocaine Use</h2>
        <p class="text-center">
            Cocaine is a powerful stimulant drug that affects the central nervous system. 
            In the UK, it remains one of the most commonly used illicit substances, particularly 
            in nightlife and social environments. Its short-term effects include increased energy, 
            alertness, and euphoria, but these effects come with serious risks.
        </p>
    </div>
</section>

<!-- Section 2 -->
<section class="section bg-light">
    <div class="container">
        <h2 class="text-center mb-5">Health Risks</h2>
        <div class="row">
            <div class="col-md-4">
                <div class="card p-4">
                    <h5>Short-Term Effects</h5>
                    <ul>
                        <li>Increased heart rate</li>
                        <li>Elevated blood pressure</li>
                        <li>Reduced appetite</li>
                        <li>Anxiety and paranoia</li>
                    </ul>
                </div>
            </div>
            <div class="col-md-4">
                <div class="card p-4">
                    <h5>Long-Term Effects</h5>
                    <ul>
                        <li>Heart disease</li>
                        <li>Mental health disorders</li>
                        <li>Respiratory issues</li>
                        <li>Addiction</li>
                    </ul>
                </div>
            </div>
            <div class="col-md-4">
                <div class="card p-4">
                    <h5>Overdose Risks</h5>
                    <ul>
                        <li>Cardiac arrest</li>
                        <li>Seizures</li>
                        <li>Stroke</li>
                        <li>Sudden death</li>
                    </ul>
                </div>
            </div>
        </div>
    </div>
</section>

<!-- Section 3 -->
<section class="section">
    <div class="container">
        <h2 class="text-center mb-4">Legal Status in the UK</h2>
        <p class="text-center">
            Cocaine is classified as a Class A drug in the UK. Possession, supply, and production 
            are illegal and carry severe penalties. Possession can result in up to 7 years in prison, 
            while supply and production can lead to life imprisonment. Law enforcement continues 
            to actively combat drug trafficking and misuse.
        </p>
    </div>
</section>

<!-- Section 4 -->
<section class="section bg-light">
    <div class="container">
        <h2 class="text-center mb-4">Social Impact</h2>
        <p class="text-center">
            Cocaine use impacts not only individuals but also society as a whole. It contributes 
            to crime, healthcare strain, and economic costs. Communities affected by drug misuse 
            often experience increased violence and instability. Addressing these issues requires 
            awareness, education, and support systems.
        </p>
    </div>
</section>

<!-- Section 5 -->
<section class="section">
